ANNOUNCEMENTS (03): PROMED-MAIL SEEKING ANIMAL HEALTH LIAISON MODERATOR
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tues 25 Jun 2013
From: Larry Madoff <lmadoff@promedmail.org>


ProMED-mail, the Program for Monitoring Emerging Diseases of the International Society for Infectious Diseases, is seeking a highly qualified individual to fill the newly created position of International Animal Health Liaison Moderator. The individual will join an international team of over 40 global health specialists located in 25 countries.

Responsibilities
----------------
1. Monitor and post relevant reports from international animal health agencies on ProMED using an online dashboard tool in a timely way (less than 24 hours).
2. Respond to specific requests for posting of animal health reports communicated by ProMED participants and staff.
3. Provide appropriate contextual commentary and background for these reports.
4. Communicate information to international health organizations in the context of rumor tracking activities including those undertaken in collaboration with OIE, WHO, and FAO.
5. Attend periodic meetings (annual or biannual) of ProMED staff.
6. Maintain expertise in animal infectious diseases through continuing education.
7. Assistance in training of new staff.
8. Assistance in recruitment of new subscribers and outreach at local and regional professional conferences and meetings.

Qualifications
--------------
1. An advanced degree in veterinary sciences (DVM or equivalent) required, additional advanced degree in a related field preferred.
2. Extensive experience in animal infectious diseases particularly in the agricultural and aquaculture sectors.
3. Thorough acquaintance with OIE's listed diseases (terrestrial, and preferably also aquatic), their epidemiology, etiology, prevention and control, history, geographical distribution, international trade implications, updated research, etc., in addition to good knowledge of OIE's relevant Code chapters and manuals. Experience/background with State Veterinary Service(s) and acquaintance with the relevant OIE working/ad-hoc groups dealing with the respective diseases/issues preferred.
4. A track record of achievement in academic, governmental, or nongovernmental organization commensurate with career stage.
5. Fluency in written and spoken English and strong written communication skills; skills in other languages a plus.
6. Skillful in use of Internet resources and facility with electronic communication.

The position requires daily monitoring of e-mail and websites and several hours of work per week. Compensation is a modest stipend paid quarterly, reimbursement for Internet expenses, and travel to ProMED-mail staff/editorial meetings.

Please send a cover letter and curriculum vitae to <info@isid.org>

--
Larry Madoff, MD
Editor, ProMED-mail
<lmadoff@promedmail.org>

